---
import Base from '@/layouts/Base.astro';
export const prerender = true;
---

<Base locale="en" title="History | AB 1889">
  <!-- Hero -->
  <div class="relative w-full">
    <img
      src="/images/about-history-hero.png"
      alt="AB 1889 History"
      class="w-full h-auto block"
      loading="eager"
    />
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[linear-gradient(to_bottom,rgba(0,0,0,0.1)_30%,rgba(0,0,0,0.55)_100%)]"></div>
    <div class="absolute inset-0 flex items-end px-8 lg:px-20 pb-14">
      <h1 class="font-black text-white leading-none text-[clamp(3.5rem,10vw,8rem)] tracking-[-0.04em]">History</h1>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 1883: White bg — text left, image right -->
  <section class="bg-white py-[clamp(64px,9vw,112px)]">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-8 lg:px-20">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 lg:gap-28 items-center">
        <div>
          <div class="inline-flex items-center mb-7 bg-ab-beige rounded-full py-[9px] px-[22px]">
            <span class="font-black text-[1.4rem] text-[#111] tracking-[-0.04em]">1883</span>
          </div>
          <h2 class="font-black mb-7 text-[clamp(1.75rem,4vw,2.75rem)] tracking-[-0.04em] leading-[1.05] text-[#111]">Well-known AB colors in green and white.</h2>
          <p class="text-[1.1rem] leading-[1.75] text-[#444] max-w-[44ch]">
            When the disciples of the Frederician Latin School became students in 1883 and moved to Copenhagen, they brought more than academic knowledge with them. Since football had not yet fully taken hold in Denmark, these students instead started a Cricket Club as a gathering point for their sporting activities.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[1.1rem] leading-[1.75] text-[#444] max-w-[44ch] mt-5">
            This club was named "Fredericia-studenternes Kricketklub" (FSK), as a final tribute to their old school. The players' uniforms were already in the familiar AB colours: Green and white.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-md aspect-[4/3]">
          <img src="/images/about-frederician-latin-school-building.png" alt="Frederician Latin School" class="w-full h-full object-cover" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 1887: Beige bg — image left, text right -->
  <section class="bg-ab-beige py-[clamp(64px,9vw,112px)]">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-8 lg:px-20">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 lg:gap-28 items-center">
        <div class="overflow-hidden order-2 lg:order-1 rounded-md aspect-[4/3]">
          <img src="/images/about-board-of-directors.png" alt="AB team 1887" class="w-full h-full object-cover" />
        </div>
        <div class="order-1 lg:order-2">
          <div class="inline-flex items-center mb-7 bg-ab-neon rounded-full py-[9px] px-[22px]">
            <span class="font-black text-[1.4rem] text-[#111] tracking-[-0.04em]">1887</span>
          </div>
          <h2 class="font-black mb-7 text-[clamp(1.75rem,4vw,2.75rem)] tracking-[-0.04em] leading-[1.05] text-[#111]">Admitted to FSK in 1887</h2>
          <p class="text-[1.1rem] leading-[1.75] text-[#111] max-w-[44ch]">
            As early as 1887, the game of football was admitted to the FSK. This happened after a Danish translation of the laws of the English Football Association had been made in the autumn of 1886/87.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[1.1rem] leading-[1.75] text-[#111] max-w-[44ch] mt-5">
            Gradually, the influx of Copenhageners increased, and it was therefore agreed that the name of the club no longer represented its members. On 26 February 1889, the "Fredericia-studenternes Kricketklub" merged with the slightly younger "Polyteknisk Klub". The name then became: Akademisk Boldklub.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 1889: Light gray bg — text left, image right -->
  <section class="bg-[#E7E7E7] py-[clamp(64px,9vw,112px)]">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-8 lg:px-20">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 lg:gap-28 items-center">
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-black mb-7 text-[clamp(1.75rem,4vw,2.75rem)] tracking-[-0.04em] leading-[1.05] text-[#111]">Newly established academic football club requirements</h2>
          <p class="text-[1.1rem] leading-[1.75] text-[#444] max-w-[44ch]">
            The entry requirements for becoming a member of the newly established Academic Football Club were changed after the merger so that anyone who had taken an entrance exam to a university or polytechnic could become a member. This also applied to students from other Scandinavian universities.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[1.1rem] leading-[1.75] text-[#444] max-w-[44ch] mt-5">
            In addition, non-academic football players with potential could be admitted to AB by being unanimously proposed by the board or by 15 members of the club.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-md aspect-[4/3]">
          <img src="/images/about-stadium-seat.png" alt="AB stadium" class="w-full h-full object-cover" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 1889 black: Board of directors -->
  <section class="bg-rich-black py-[clamp(64px,9vw,112px)]">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-8 lg:px-20">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 lg:gap-28 items-center">
        <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-md aspect-[4/3]">
          <img src="/images/about-board-of-directors.png" alt="AB board of directors 1889" class="w-full h-full object-cover" />
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="inline-flex items-center mb-7 bg-ab-green rounded-full py-[9px] px-[22px]">
            <span class="font-black text-[1.4rem] text-white tracking-[-0.04em]">1889</span>
          </div>
          <h2 class="font-black mb-7 text-[clamp(1.75rem,4vw,2.75rem)] tracking-[-0.04em] leading-[1.05] text-ab-beige">AB's new board of directors</h2>
          <p class="text-[1.1rem] leading-[1.75] text-ab-beige mb-4">AB's new board of directors after the merger consisted of:</p>
          <ul class="flex flex-col gap-2 text-ab-beige text-[1.1rem] leading-[1.75]">
            <li>ME Pagh — Chairman (former Chairman of the Fredericia Students' Cricket Club)</li>
            <li>E. Faber</li>
            <li>H. Forchhammer</li>
            <li>H.C. Lund</li>
            <li>H. Birk</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 1889 white: Two columns -->
  <section class="bg-white py-[clamp(64px,9vw,112px)]">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-8 lg:px-20">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 lg:gap-28 items-start">
        <div>
          <div class="inline-flex items-center mb-7 bg-ab-green rounded-full py-[9px] px-[22px]">
            <span class="font-black text-[1.4rem] text-white tracking-[-0.04em]">1889</span>
          </div>
          <h2 class="font-black mb-7 text-[clamp(1.75rem,4vw,2.75rem)] tracking-[-0.04em] leading-[1.05] text-[#111]">Contingency of 50 ORE per month in 1889</h2>
          <p class="text-[1.1rem] leading-[1.75] text-[#444]">In 1889, the membership fee for active members of AB was just 50 øre per month.</p>
          <p class="text-[1.1rem] leading-[1.75] text-[#444] mt-5">
            On 1 April 1889, the club moved to new premises at Helgesensgade 5, where they were well received by the club's first clothing sponsor. Since they could not afford to buy new towels, a mother of an AB player bought fabric on credit and sewed 6 towels herself, which she happily handed to the enthusiastic players.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[1.1rem] leading-[1.75] text-[#444] mt-5">
            DBU acquired a nice trophy for the tidy sum of 150 kroons, and the result of DBU's first tournament (1889–1890) was that AB won the final over KB 2-0.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[1.1rem] leading-[1.75] text-[#444] mt-5">
            Around the turn of the century, both KB and B93 had their own pitches, and AB thought that they should have one too. The necessary capital — 60,000 DKK — was obtained from the club's supporters, and it was then possible to rent an area on Lammefælleden on Tagensvej from the Municipality of Copenhagen, completed in 1903.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="pt-[calc(1.4rem+18px+1.75rem)]">
          <h2 class="font-black mb-7 text-[clamp(1.75rem,4vw,2.75rem)] tracking-[-0.04em] leading-[1.05] text-[#111]">One of the greatest personalities in AB</h2>
          <p class="text-[1.1rem] leading-[1.75] text-[#444]">
            One of the greatest personalities of this time in AB was Department Head Charles Buchwald, who played all three ball games available at AB: football, tennis and cricket. Buchwald played on the national team in football and cricket and was club champion in tennis.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[1.1rem] leading-[1.75] text-[#444] mt-5">
            Buchwald made his debut on AB's first team in football at the age of 16, the same age as Harald Bohr, who made it to 4 international matches. His brother Niels, who probably became better known outside the pitch, was a goalkeeper.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[1.1rem] leading-[1.75] text-[#444] mt-5">
            'AB was quite superior in a match against a selected German team — Mittweida — and Niels Bohr made the time pass by standing and leaning on one of the goalposts. Suddenly a long ball was kicked towards AB's goal. Everyone expected Niels to go out and take the ball, but he did nothing. After the match he had to admit that his thoughts were about a mathematical problem.'
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 1894: Green bg — crest left, text right -->
  <section class="bg-ab-green py-[clamp(64px,9vw,112px)]">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-8 lg:px-20">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 lg:gap-28 items-center">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center aspect-square max-h-[500px]">
          <img src="/images/about-crest-original.png" alt="AB 1889 crest" class="w-[min(480px,90%)]" />
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="inline-flex items-center mb-7 bg-ab-neon rounded-full py-[9px] px-[22px]">
            <span class="font-black text-[1.4rem] text-[#111] tracking-[-0.04em]">1894</span>
          </div>
          <h2 class="font-black mb-7 text-[clamp(1.75rem,4vw,2.75rem)] tracking-[-0.04em] leading-[1.05] text-white">Establishment of junior department in 1894</h2>
          <p class="text-[1.1rem] leading-[1.75] text-white/85">
            Since the new game had not yet reached the schools, the club tried in 1894 to establish a Junior Department, which was not a great success. In 1899 AB tried again. This time under the leadership of the creator of AB's famous junior department and its leader for 20 years — Edmond Andersen.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[1.1rem] leading-[1.75] text-white/85 mt-5">
            During the department's first year of existence, the number of members increased to almost 70. Edmond Andersen kept a careful diary of the individual training sessions — both big and small.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
